<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-67-0090 </DOCNO><TEXT>The role is assessed of computerized tomography in cerebrovascular diagnosis.It is pointed out to be the only imaging technique directly visualizingthe brain parenchyma and its pathological changes. It is capable of earlyand accurate visualization of infarctions and hematomas and of differentiatingbetween ischemic and hemorrhagic lesions, and thus affecting management.It is seen as a noninvasive technique usable for patients irrespectiveof their condition as the most suitable and in most cases also completelysatisfactory examination. (L.O.). 1 fig., 2 refs.</TEXT></DOC>